Indeed, the etymology of the word leads irresistibly to the conclusion which I adopt: scearu, share or portion, is used over and over again to denote the estate or land of a particular person; and folc- scearu is the general or public share, as folcriht is the public law, (folces folcriht, No, ccxcv1,) folctoga the public leader,—compounds in which folc is equivalent to peo'd in such words as peo‘dcyning, peo‘dsceaoa, pefid- loga.
